se your phone if you’re in a pinch.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"keeps-you-from-relying-on-public-charging-stations\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e4 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Keeps You From Relying on Public Charging Stations\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThere’s nothing wrong with using a secure public charging station. But the reality is that if you’re in a crowded place, you’re unlikely to find one with free ports. Even if you find an unoccupied charging station, your phone won’t charge as fast as it does at home. This means you’re essentially just stuck waiting around the charging station for your phone to power on.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eBeyond that, security risks like \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/what-is-juice-jacking/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ejuice jacking\u003c/a\u003e have really turned me off public charging stations. I don’t want to risk data theft or malware exposure because I forgot to charge my phone. I’d much rather carry a power portable bank to charge my phone anytime the battery drops too much.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"protects-your-phone-39-s-battery\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e3 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Protects Your Phone\u0026#39;s Battery\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                                                                        \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/a-power-bank-with-a-low-battery-icon.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id